                {
                    "id" : "navigation",
                    "text" : "<p><table class=\"book_navigation\"><tr><td><span id=\"htPrevText\"></span></td> <td> <span id=\"htTopText\"></span> </td> <td><span id=\"htNextText\"></span></td></tr><tr><td><a href=\"index.html?page=class_content&arg=489f9dbf-f251-4ef8-a61b-431564784bd5\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('class_content', 'html', '489f9dbf-f251-4ef8-a61b-431564784bd5', false); return false;\">Our sides are equal</a></td> <td><a href=\"index.html?page=first_steps&arg=\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('first_steps','html', '', false); return false;\"><span id=\"htIndexText\"></span></a></td><td><a href=\"index.html?page=class_content&arg=7fe341a9-420e-4318-be3e-c7c201d821a8\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('class_content', 'html', '7fe341a9-420e-4318-be3e-c7c201d821a8', false); return false;\">Beyond fingers</a></td></tr></table></p>"
                },
                {
                    "id" : "introduction",
                    "text" : [ "<p><h3>We need couting</h3>In our lives, we always have something to count: our age, our friends, or our toys. Observe <b>Figure 1</b>, which shows indigenous musical instruments from Costa Rica:</p>", "<p class=\"desc\"> <img src=\"images/MusicCR.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\" />Figure 1: Musical instruments present in Costa Rica (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('3e4dc8f8-8c2b-491e-9e2b-0b3adb927c70'); return false;\">Museo Nacional de Costa Rica</a>). Photo taken during a visit to the museum on <span id=\"htdate0\"></span></p>", "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\">?</div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: Couting with our body</b><br />On the previous page, we began to learn about our body. Now, think: is there a part of our body that we can use to count?</div></div></center></p>" ]
                },
                {
                    "id" : "hands",
                    "text" : [ "<p><h3>Counting with our hands</h3>We can address our problem by using each finger to count a unique object:</p>", "<p><table class=\"book_navigation\"><tr><td>Left hand</td><td>Right hand</td></tr><tr><td><img src=\"images/Hand_Grape.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\"/></td><td><img src=\"images/RHand_Grape.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\"/></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\">Figure 2: Representation of our hands. Source code available on the project's GitHub (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('240800f3-ede4-4deb-9d4e-915a3a03fa68'); return false;\">History Tracers, <span id=\"htdate1\"></span>, Source code</a>)</td></tr></table></p>" ]
                },
                {
                    "id" : "testing",
                    "text" : [ "<p><h3>One by one</h3><b>Figure 1</b> as fewer musical instruments than we typically have fingers on our hands. How can we count a few objects? The first step is to become familiar with our fingers:</p>", "<p class=\"desc\"><img src=\"images/Hand_Finger.png\" class=\"imgcenter\"/>Figure 3: Fingers of a left hand: <b>A</b> - Thumb, <b>B</b> - Index, <b>C</b> - Middle, <b>D</b> - Ring, <b>E</b> - Little. The source code is available in GitHub of the project (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('240800f3-ede4-4deb-9d4e-915a3a03fa68'); return false;\">History Tracers, <span id=\"htdate2\"></span>, CÃ³digo-fonte</a>).</p>", "Now that we know our fingers, we will raise one finger at a time to do the counting:</p>", "<table class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th>Left hand</th><th>Description</th><th>Right hand</th></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/0Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">All fingers down.</td><td><img src=\"images/0Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/0Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">Right index finger raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/1Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/0Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">Index and middle fingers of the right hand raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/2Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/0Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Index, middle and ring of the right hand raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/3Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/0Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">Index, middle, ring and little of the right hand raised</td><td><img src=\"images/4Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/0Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">All fingers of the right hand raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/1Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">All fingers of the right hand raised, and index of the left hand raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/2Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">All fingers of the right hand raised, with index and middle of the left hand raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/3Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">All fingers of the right hand raised, with index, middle and ring of the left hand raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/4Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\" style=\"text-align: center;\">All fingers of the right hand raised, with index, middle, ring and little of the left hand raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> <tr><td><img src=\"images/5Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">All fingers raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr> </table>", "<p class=\"desc\">Table 1: Counting with our fingers.</p>" ]
                },
                {
                    "id" : "conclusion",
                    "text" : [ "<p><h3>Conclusion</h3>To count all the musical instruments above the bird in <b>Figure 1</b>, our fingers will look like this:</p>", "<table class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th>Left hand</th><th>Description</th><th>Right hand</th></tr>  <tr><td><img src=\"images/1Left_Hand_Small.png\" /></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\">All fingers of the right hand raised, and index of the left hand raised.</td><td><img src=\"images/5Right_Hand_Small.png\" /></td></tr></table>", "<p class=\"desc\">Table 2: Couting musical instruments in <b>Figure 1</b>.</p>", "<p class=\"lab\"><b>Practice 1: Couting around</b><br />Using your fingers, count some objects around you.</p>", "<p>As we have seen, our hands can help us count. But how can we count a quantity larger than the number of fingers we have? We will begin to explore this in the next text.</p>" ]
